modules.description: Provides compression and decompression of data streams using the BZ2 algorithm, with functions to initialize contexts, process data, and finalize output. Operates on byte sequences and handles incremental data processing. Used to compress large files efficiently or decompress data received in chunks from network sources.

Provides functions to compress and decompress data using the bzip2 algorithm, with support for reading from and writing to input and output channels. Operates on byte buffers, in_channel, and out_channel types, enabling efficient handling of compressed data streams. Supports reading unused data after a compressed stream and allows custom block sizes for compression.
